Claims CLAIMS  What is claimed is: 1. A method comprising: by a server computing device, determining whether a plurality of client computing devices are in physical proximity to one another; by the server computing device, generating respective adaptations of digital content for display by the plurality of client computing devices, wherein each of the respective content adaptations presents a different content view configured for a specific one of the client computing devices, and wherein the respective content adaptations are configured for synchronous presentation on the client computing devices; and by the server computing device, sending each of the respective content adaptations to one of the client computing devices. 2. The method of Claim 1, wherein determining whether the plurality of client computing devices are in physical proximity to one another comprises: generating a code; sending the generated code to one of the client computing devices; receiving, from an other one of the client computing devices, an image of the generated code as captured by the other one of the client computing devices; and comparing the image with the generated code to validate the other one of the client computing devices. 3. The method of Claim 1, wherein determining whether the plurality of client computing devices are in physical proximity to one another comprises, by a first one of the plurality of client computing devices, actively listening for signals indicating that a second one of the plurality of client computing devices has moved within a threshold distance of the first client computing device. 4. The method of Claim 3, wherein the signals comprise one or more types of signals adapted for close-proximity communication between devices including near field communication (NFC), infrared, Bluetooth Low Energy (BTLE), radio-frequency identification (RFI). 5. The method of Claim 1, wherein generating the respective content adaptations comprises dividing the digital content into spatial view partitions, wherein a number of spatial view partitions is equal to a number of the client computing devices, wherein each of the spatial view partitions is associated with a respective one of the client computing devices. 6. The method of Claim 1, further comprising: monitoring position orientation information for each of the client computing devices, wherein generating the content adaptations is based at least in part on the position and orientation information. 7. The method of Claim 1, further comprising: in response to receiving user input selecting the digital content from a first one of the client computing devices, generating an invitation to congregate to one or more other users each associated with a respective second one of the client computing devices, wherein the invitation specifies a physical location for viewing the digital content; sending the invitation to the second client computing devices. 8. The method of Claim 7, wherein selecting the digital content is based at least on a social affinity, status, age, location, gender, content preference, group affiliation, content viewing history, user interaction history, event attendance history, or attribute of the one or more other users. 9. The method of Claim 7, further comprising: obtaining a plurality of user profiles, wherein each of the user profiles corresponds to a user of one of the client computing devices; 

